---
# clang-tidy configuration for AdaptiveSound (C++23 / Obj-C++ real-time audio).
#
# Philosophy: enable everything (`-*` resets, then re-enable every valuable group) so
# every diagnostic is at least SURFACED, then promote all SAFETY/CORRECTNESS families to
# build-breaking errors (WarningsAsErrors below). Checks that are incompatible with
# real-time DSP buffer work, or that fight a deliberate/documented project convention, are
# disabled outright with an inline reason (guide §5.3).
#
# WarningsAsErrors is the literal guide value `'*'` — every ENABLED check is a build-breaking
# error. Because `Checks:` is an allowlist (it starts with `-*`), `'*'` here means "every
# check we chose to keep is fatal", NOT "every check clang-tidy owns". This is drift-proof:
# a family can't be enabled-but-only-warn by accident. The purely *stylistic* checks that
# would otherwise turn ~150 pre-existing findings across 17 bridge files into commit blockers
# for zero safety benefit are DISABLED outright below (with reasons), rather than promoted —
# so the '*' promotion lands on 0 pre-existing findings while still failing all NEW unsafe
# code. The stylistic-modernize backlog is deferred to a dedicated sweep (§5.3: don't enable
# rules incompatible with the work).
#
# clang-tidy runs on STAGED files in the pre-commit hook (.githooks/pre-commit); the
# strict-gate uses clang-format + build -Werror + sanitizers as the repo-wide C++ net.
Checks: >
  -*,
  bugprone-*,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -bugprone-exception-escape,
  cert-*,
  -cert-err09-cpp,
  -cert-err61-cpp,
  -cert-err33-c,
  clang-analyzer-*,
  concurrency-*,
  -concurrency-mt-unsafe,
  cppcoreguidelines-*,
  -cppcoreguidelines-owning-memory,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-array-to-pointer-decay,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-avoid-unchecked-container-access,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-constant-array-index,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-pointer-arithmetic,
  -cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-reinterpret-cast,
  modernize-*,
  -modernize-use-auto,
  -modernize-use-trailing-return-type,
  -modernize-use-std-print,
  -modernize-use-using,
  -modernize-use-designated-initializers,
  -modernize-use-equals-delete,
  -modernize-use-integer-sign-comparison,
  -modernize-deprecated-headers,
  -modernize-return-braced-init-list,
  performance-*,
  portability-*,
  -portability-simd-intrinsics,
  -portability-avoid-pragma-once,
  readability-*,
  -readability-magic-numbers

# Every ENABLED check (see the `-*`-anchored allowlist above) is a build-breaking error.
# The stylistic-only checks are disabled in Checks, so this promotion lands on 0 pre-existing
# findings — literal-guide '*' with no landmines and no two-list drift.
WarningsAsErrors: "*"

# --- Why each disable exists (all are either RT-audio-incompatible or non-goals) ---
#   bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters  DSP APIs legitimately take several same-typed
#                                         (float/size_t) params (freq, Q, gain, frames).
#   bugprone-exception-escape             Target builds -fno-exceptions; the check is moot.
#   cert-err09-cpp / cert-err61-cpp       Exception-handling CERT rules; -fno-exceptions.
#   cert-err33-c                          Disabled as a redundant ALIAS of bugprone-unused-
#                                         return-value: it fires on the same broad C-stdlib set
#                                         (std::remove, fwrite, the printf family, etc.), not
#                                         "only fprintf/snprintf". Precise dangerous-unchecked-
#                                         return coverage is provided instead by the explicit
#                                         bugprone-unused-return-value.CheckedFunctions list
#                                         (parse / IO / alloc functions) in CheckOptions below,
#                                         with AllowCastToVoid as the (void)-cast escape hatch.
#   concurrency-mt-unsafe                 Flags getenv/strerror etc. in non-RT setup code;
#                                         the RT path is guarded by review + TSan, not this.
#   cppcoreguidelines-owning-memory       No GSL dependency; ownership is enforced by RAII
#                                         + opaque-handle design, not gsl::owner annotations.
#   cppcoreguidelines-pro-bounds-*        Raw float* buffer arithmetic and constant array
#                                         indexing are intrinsic to vDSP/Accelerate kernels;
#                                         .at() throws (banned under -fno-exceptions).
#   cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-reinterpret-cast  Required at the Swift/C++/CoreAudio
#                                         AudioBufferList boundary (interleaved float bytes).
#   modernize-use-auto                    Project prefers explicit types in DSP math for
#                                         readability of fixed-width/precision intent.
#   modernize-use-trailing-return-type    Purely stylistic; the codebase uses conventional
#                                         leading-return-type declarations throughout. Not a
#                                         safety/correctness check — promoting it would force
#                                         a repo-wide rewrite with zero behavioural benefit.
#   modernize-use-std-print               fprintf(stderr,…) is the documented off-RT-thread
#                                         diagnostic-logging convention (DEVELOPMENT.md).
#                                         std::print is not guaranteed on the Apple libc++
#                                         deployment target and the rewrite adds no value.
#   modernize-use-using                   } Purely STYLISTIC modernize checks. The codebase
#   modernize-use-designated-initializers } predates them (typedef, {}-init, private-unimpl
#   modernize-use-equals-delete           } special members, <stdio.h>). ~150 pre-existing
#   modernize-use-integer-sign-comparison } findings across 17 bridge files, zero safety
#   modernize-deprecated-headers          } value. Disabled here so WarningsAsErrors:'*' has
#   modernize-return-braced-init-list     } no landmines; deferred to a dedicated style sweep.
#   portability-simd-intrinsics           Apple-Silicon-only target (arm64). Deliberate
#                                         Accelerate/vDSP + NEON use; cross-arch portability
#                                         is an explicit non-goal, so the warning is noise.
#   portability-avoid-pragma-once         Apple-Clang-only target; `#pragma once` is
#                                         universally supported and is a project header
#                                         convention. Cross-compiler portability is a non-goal.
#   readability-magic-numbers             RBJ biquad / psychoacoustic formulas contain
#                                         intrinsic structural constants; semantic ones are
#                                         already named. See CheckOptions below.

HeaderFilterRegex: "Sources/AudioDSP.*\\.h|Tests/.*\\.(inc|h)"
FormatStyle: file
CheckOptions:
  - key: readability-identifier-naming.VariableCase
    value: camelBack
  - key: readability-identifier-naming.FunctionCase
    value: camelBack
  - key: readability-identifier-naming.ClassCase
    value: CamelCase
  # Accept k-prefixed constexpr constants (e.g. kMaxBiquads) without renaming.
  - key: readability-identifier-naming.ConstexprVariableCase
    value: CamelCase
  - key: readability-identifier-naming.ConstexprVariablePrefix
    value: k
  # RBJ Audio EQ Cookbook canonical single-letter amplitude (A) and Q-factor (Q)
  # locals: keep the cookbook notation rather than forcing camelBack renames.
  - key: readability-identifier-naming.LocalVariableIgnoredRegexp
    value: '^(A|Q)$'
  # DSP process() functions legitimately branch on channel/biquad/gain state.
  # 10 is unrealistically low; 25 still catches genuinely unmaintainable code.
  - key: readability-function-cognitive-complexity.Threshold
    value: 25
  - key: performance-move-const-arg.CheckTriviallyCopyableMove
    value: false
  - key: bugprone-narrowing-conversions.PedanticMode
    value: true
  # bugprone-unused-return-value: narrow the default STL-centric list down to the functions
  # where an IGNORED return is a genuine silent bug — parse (strto*/ato*/*scanf), IO
  # (fread/fgets) and allocation (malloc/calloc/realloc/aligned_alloc/posix_memalign). This is
  # the precise unchecked-return coverage that replaces the redundant cert-err33-c alias
  # (disabled above). posix_memalign is the codebase's ACTUAL over-aligned allocator
  # (Tests/SoakRtAllocTests.inc): unlike malloc it returns an int ERROR CODE and leaves the
  # out-pointer INDETERMINATE on failure, so an unchecked call is doubly dangerous — the
  # existing callsite already checks `!= 0`, so this adds 0 findings today while catching any
  # future unchecked use. (aligned_alloc stays as the standard C11 sibling.)
  # AllowCastToVoid gives an explicit `(void)fn();` escape hatch for a deliberate discard.
  - key: bugprone-unused-return-value.CheckedFunctions
    value: '::strtol;::strtoll;::strtoul;::strtoull;::strtof;::strtod;::strtold;::atoi;::atol;::atoll;::atof;::scanf;::sscanf;::fscanf;::fread;::fgets;::malloc;::calloc;::realloc;::aligned_alloc;::posix_memalign'
  - key: bugprone-unused-return-value.AllowCastToVoid
    value: 'true'
  # RBJ Audio EQ Cookbook uses canonical single-letter DSP notation:
  #   A = amplitude (sqrt of linear gain), Q = quality factor, w0 = angular freq.
  # Allow these specific names rather than obscuring them with verbose renames.
  - key: readability-identifier-length.MinimumVariableNameLength
    value: 2
  - key: readability-identifier-length.IgnoredVariableNames
    value: '^(A|Q|b|i|j|w0)$'
  - key: readability-identifier-length.IgnoredParameterNames
    value: '^(A|Q|b|i|j)$'
  # Structural 0/1/2 and -2.0 in RBJ biquad formulas are intrinsic, not magic;
  # keep clang-tidy defaults 1.0/100.0 too. DSP-semantic literals are named.
  - key: cppcoreguidelines-avoid-magic-numbers.IgnoredFloatingPointValues
    value: '0.0;1.0;2.0;100.0'
  # NOTE: no GSL dependency exists and the pro-bounds-* checks above are
  # disabled (incompatible with -fno-exceptions RT audio: .at() throws,
  # raw float* buffer arithmetic is intrinsic). GslHeader option removed.

UseColor: true
